    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "i was just staring at the ceiling for like two hours thinking about how everything is just... nothing. like, we're just these tiny, accidental sparks of consciousness that exist for a second and then just vanish into the dark. doesn't it feel kind of exhausting to just keep pretending that any of this actually matters?",
